  "text": "for Pediatric Radiology and published in 1995 [CITATION_1] . This list of approximately 320 pediatric diseases and teaching topics was used as a starting point for the medical knowledge component of the curriculum. Through a two-part needs assessment designed by a medical educator and biostatistician, 20 radiology resident volunteers and five faculty radiologists with 5-25 years' teaching experience from a large academic medical center refined the topics for medical content and method of delivery of the program (Table 1) .",
